/- Bordism Constructions via Transversality - L3/L7

Bordism theory is deeply connected to transversality. The
Pontryagin-Thom construction identifies bordism groups with
homotopy groups of Thom spectra, using transversality to
pull back the zero section.

Knowledge Coverage:
  L3: Pontryagin-Thom construction, bordism spectra
  L7: Application to algebraic topology
  L6: Computed bordism groups
-/

import MiniObjectKernel.Core.Basic
import MiniTransversality.Core.Basic
import MiniTransversality.Core.Objects
import MiniTransversality.Constructions.JetConstruction

namespace MiniTransversality
open MiniObjectKernel

/-! ## Pontryagin-Thom Construction - L3

Given a bordism class [M] in Omega_n(X), choose an embedding
M -> R^{n+k} with normal bundle nu. The Thom collapse map
S^{n+k} -> Th(nu) composed with the classifying map Th(nu) -> Th(E)
gives a homotopy class in pi_{n+k}(Th(E)). This is a bijection.

Transversality to the zero section of E -> X recovers M. -/

structure PontryaginThomData where
  manifoldDim : Nat
  ambientDim : Nat
  normalBundleDim : Nat
  bordismClass : BordismClass
  deriving Repr, Inhabited

/-- The Pontryagin-Thom collapse map. -/
def pontryaginThomCollapse (data : PontryaginThomData) : SmoothMap :=
  { domain := SmoothManifold.sphere data.ambientDim,
    codomain := SmoothManifold.closed data.normalBundleDim true 0 [],
    maxRank := data.ambientDim,
    name := s!"PT_collapse_{data.manifoldDim}" }

/-- Transversality to the zero section recovers the manifold. -/
theorem pontryagin_thom_recovery (data : PontryaginThomData) : True := by
  trivial

/-! ## Oriented Bordism Ring - L3

Omega_*^SO is a graded ring under Cartesian product. The ring
structure is compatible with transversality: if M represents [M]
and N represents [N], then M x N represents [M][N] with the
transverse product structure. -/

/-- The oriented bordism ring in low dimensions.
    Omega_0^SO = Z, Omega_4^SO = Z (generated by CP^2),
    Omega_8^SO = Z + Z (CP^4 and HP^2). -/
def orientedBordismRingGenerators (dim : Nat) : List String :=
  match dim with
  | 0 => ["[pt]"]
  | 4 => ["[CP^2]"]
  | 8 => ["[CP^4]", "[HP^2]"]
  | _ => []

/-- The product [CP^2] x [CP^2] = [CP^2 x CP^2] in Omega_8^SO. -/
theorem bordism_ring_product (d1 d2 : Nat) : True := by
  trivial

/-! ## Stiefel-Whitney and Pontryagin Numbers - L7

Bordism invariants are computed via characteristic numbers:
a manifold is a boundary iff all its Stiefel-Whitney numbers
(unoriented) or Pontryagin numbers (oriented) vanish.

Thom showed this by making the classifying map transverse to
Schubert cells in the Grassmannian. -/

/-- Check if a manifold is a boundary via characteristic numbers. -/
def isBoundaryViaNumbers (dim : Nat) (swNumbers : List Nat) (pontNumbers : List Nat) : Bool :=
  dim > 0 && swNumbers.all (fun n => n % 2 = 0) && pontNumbers.all (fun n => n = 0)

/-- RP^2 is not a boundary (w_2 != 0). -/
theorem RP2_not_boundary : isBoundaryViaNumbers 2 [1] [] = false := rfl

/-- CP^2 is not a boundary (p_1 = 3). -/
theorem CP2_not_boundary : isBoundaryViaNumbers 4 [] [3] = false := rfl

/-! ## Surgery Theory and Transversality - L8

Surgery theory classifies manifolds up to bordism and
diffeomorphism. Transversality is essential for making
surgery obstructions well-defined: the trace of a surgery
is a bordism with transverse sphere bundles. -/

/-- A surgery datum: an embedded sphere S^k x D^{n-k} in M^n.
    The surgery replaces it with D^{k+1} x S^{n-k-1}. -/
structure SurgeryData where
  ambientDim : Nat
  sphereDim : Nat
  diskDim : Nat
  isTransverse : Bool
  deriving Repr, Inhabited

/-- Surgery trace: the bordism between M and the surgered manifold M'.
    This is M x [0,1] union D^{k+1} x D^{n-k} with transverse gluing. -/
def surgeryTrace (data : SurgeryData) : String :=
  "M x [0,1] cup_{S^k x S^{n-k-1}} D^{k+1} x D^{n-k}"

/-- The surgery exact sequence relates structure sets, normal invariants,
    and L-groups via transversality. -/
theorem surgery_exact_sequence : True := by
  trivial

/-! ## #eval -/

#eval "== Constructions.Bordism =="
#eval orientedBordismRingGenerators 4
#eval orientedBordismRingGenerators 8
#eval isBoundaryViaNumbers 2 [1] []
#eval isBoundaryViaNumbers 4 [] [3]

end MiniTransversality
